name: 04-Model Training and Validation
content:
Model Training and Validation

Model Used:

  • K-means Clustering – Groups customers into distinct clusters based on behavioral and demographic features.
  • Prediction Model – Saved clustering model is reused to classify new customers into existing clusters.

Feature Details:

  • Core clustering inputs: MonthlyRevenue, MonthlyMinutes, OverageMinutes, CustomerCareCalls, DroppedCalls, RetentionCalls, MonthsInService.
  • Demographics and equipment details used for profiling post-clustering.

Feature Importance:

  • Though clustering does not assign feature weights like supervised models, feature relevance is evaluated using:
  • Cluster centroids for continuous features (e.g., revenue, minutes).
  • Distribution comparison across clusters for categorical features (e.g., churn, service area).

Model Metrics & Validation:

  • Elbow Method & Silhouette Score – Used to determine the optimal number of clusters.
  • Cluster Cohesion – Measure intra-cluster similarity.
  • Cluster Separation – Ensure meaningful differentiation across groups.
